node.text: This interview, hosted by @coachdhillon (give him a follow!), covers how I built the @investearnsave page into a profitable business in just 1 year, as well as my thoughts on themes such as investing, education and self-development. It was a pleasure to be on his podcast and we decided to share it here to give it extra visibility.

node.text:
Some variation of this is something all entrepreneurs experience...⁣
⁣
You also have a rollercoaster of perceptions too.⁣
⁣
At first you think a certain goal will make you feel happy and successful, and for a short time when you reach it you will.⁣
⁣
Then you end up networking with people doing way better than you and you see you have far to go.⁣
⁣
Then you hit some kind of roadblock, maybe you have a bad month or an event affects your business, you feel like you've completely failed then even though you're still way ahead of where you were when you first started.⁣
⁣
You just need to learn to remove yourself from the situation, meditate on it and realise as long as you're putting in the work to progress, that's all that matters.⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣
Don’t miss a post 👉 @investearnsave⁣⁣
⁣

node.text:
Two of the world's richest men are afraid of Google, but why?...⁣
⁣
Google is a company that is ingrained into our psyche. It's almost an extension of our brain to "Google" something. ⁣
⁣
There's no other company that has achieved the ability to become a literal part of our being so effectively.⁣
⁣
Not just that, they have more data than any Government, and probably more data than almost every other company combined. Perhaps with the exception of Facebook.⁣
⁣
They also have their hands in everything from military tech to trying to achieve immortality.⁣
⁣
My purpose isn't to scare you or to make a comment on Google's intentions, just to show you how powerful they have become as a company.⁣
⁣
And how did they do it?⁣
⁣
Simple.⁣
⁣
They made life 100x easier for us. And they did it with the most friendly UI (think of how Bing, Yahoo, etc looks compared to Google's design).⁣
⁣
There will be opportunities to build such companies in future and maybe even now.⁣
⁣
Food for thought.⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣
Don’t miss a post 👉 @investearnsave⁣⁣
⁣
#Google #LarryPage #ElonMusk #JeffBezos #Amazon #Coporations #CorporatePower

node.text:
You don't even need to believe in destiny to believe in destiny. 🤯Okay, hear me out...⁣
⁣
If overtime you build a conviction that your life will turn out well, that you'll be able to achieve your dreams, meet the right people, live a good life. And you start working on good habits that will help you move towards it, chances are it will happen.⁣
⁣
Literally if you can just convince yourself of these things, the chances of them happening is way higher.⁣
⁣
This is because your thoughts and decisions will occur with this conviction in mind, thus meaning you will push your own life towards these good things.⁣
⁣
It's not the law of attraction, it's just realising the power you have over your own life and your own destiny, and that self-belief goes a long, long way.⁣
⁣⁣⁣

node.text:
This is truer than people realize...⁣
⁣
Everyone has a million and one excuses why they don't start a business, start investing, start writing, start a YouTube channel, etc etc.⁣
⁣
But most people do not acknowledge that embarrassment is one of their reasons for not starting.⁣
⁣
And it is embarrassing. For people you know to see your project before it is successful.⁣
⁣
However, it is essential you overcome this.⁣
⁣
And once you've overcome it once, you become fearless in future.⁣
⁣
Remember: society wants everyone to be the same, those who stick their neck out above the crowd will always be judged and shamed.⁣
⁣
But it's those people that stick their necks out, those who overcome the fear of starting from the bottom that go on to achieve great things and live incredible lives.⁣
⁣
P.s; I can't actually find a reliable source for this quote actually been said, despite seeing it quoted often, so keep that in mind. It's a good quote regardless which is why I'm sharing it.⁣
